$AAPL $GOOGL $MSFT $FB EU reaches deal on new digital competition law, WSJ reports 06:18 
 
Lawmakers in Europe have reached an agreement on the main points of the Digital Markets Act, a new digital competition law focused on the world's biggest tech companies, The Wall Street Journal's Kim Mackrael and Sam Schechner report. The legislation seeks to impose new obligations and prohibitions on digital giants the EU calls "gatekeepers" in order to limit the ability of tech companies to take advantage of their presence in digital markets. Provisions would allow developers to make their apps available to iPhone users without going through Apple's (AAPL) App Store and could limit how sites such as Google (GOOGL) and Amazon (AMZN) can rank their own products and services ahead of those offered by smaller competitors in search results, according to the report. The Wall Street Journal previously said Facebook (FB), Microsoft (MSFT), Booking (BKNG) and Alibaba (BABA) would be impacted.
